    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>I am much obliged to you for three favors all of much use. Please to make a
                    little bill for the money you have laid out &amp; I will send you a draft. I
                    wonder we hear nothing of <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Low</persName>. I hope he is not ill. do not trouble you about <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0159">Lord Hails book</title></bibl>. I can
                    get it here readier from <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>. I thank you
                    for the hint about repetition which shall be fully attended to. The two first
                    volumes of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">new edition of Br.
                            Zool</title></bibl> are almost printed. I presume it will appear in
                    spring. the q<hi rend="superscript">to</hi> will be very handsome.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>very affect<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi> y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>.

                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Nov<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> 7<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1775.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
